  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2026-03-17",
    "date": "2026-04-14T18:35:16Z",
    "text": "Export Dispute Resolution Act\n\nThis bill revises the interagency dispute resolution process for export license applications. In particular, the bill requires the Operating Committee for Export Policy (an interagency body within the Department of Commerce's Bureau of Industry and Security) to resolve disputes related to specified matters by majority vote, including matters relating to countries that are subject to comprehensive U.S. arms\u00a0embargoes.\n\nThe bill also authorizes the\u00a0committee chair to decide cases and matters that cannot be decided by majority vote."
  },
